items.name: DIY Culture
items.title: DIY Culture
items.headline: Welcome to the DIY Culture Wiki
items.desc: Do It Yourself, or DIY, is a term that is used by various communities of practice that focus on people creating things for themselves without the aid of a paid professional. DIY has a lengthy history around the world, since through the ages of camp life, and later village and town life, the most common situation has been for people to use local technologies to take care of their needs for themselves (and, for most of the centuries now past, even to make their own tools, clothing and so on). Check out the wiki now for some great DIY tips!

items.name: The Firefly and Serenity Database
items.title: The Firefly and Serenity Database
items.headline: Welcome to The Firefly and Serenity Database!
items.desc:
Welcome to the encyclopedia based on Joss Whedon's series and film that anyone can edit.

Firefly is a science fiction television series that premiered in the United States and Canada on September 20, 2002. Its naturalistic future setting, modeled after traditional Western movie motifs, presents an atypical science fiction backdrop for the narrative. It was conceived by writer and director Joss Whedon, creator of Buffy the Vampire Slayer and Angel, under his production tag, Mutant Enemy.

Serenity is a 2005 science-fiction film written and directed by Joss Whedon. It is set in the universe of the canceled Fox science fiction television series Firefly, taking place a few months after the events of the final episode.

Read about the latest in matches, T.V. episodes, tag teams, merchandise and more!

items.desc:
The eWrestling Encyclopedia is the first fully interactive e-wrestling knowledge base. It was formed in July of 2005, and is hosted by Wikia.
As an editable website, EWE is a collaborative attempt to document the past, present and future of everything related to the 'hobby' of e-wrestling. This includes information on the characters, federations, inter-federations and handlers and anything which can be written about to an acceptable level.

The eWrestling Encyclopedia strives to change the face of e-wrestling, and to prevent the inevitable situation where the stars of today will be forgotten in ten years time. We plan to become an indispensable tool to all handlers and e-federation fanatics, and with your help, we might be able to do just that.

items.name: Adobe Premiere Pro
items.title: Adobe Premiere Pro
items.headline: Get Help with Adobe Premiere Pro
items.desc:
Having a problem with Adobe Premiere Pro?  You've come to the right place, we can help you trouble shoot the issues.

Some Quick Tips
    Remove all Adobe beta software installed on your computer. For CS4 see here. For CS3 see here. 

    Ensure your OS is set to display at least 32bit color. Lower display settings are known to cause problems. 

    If you are using more than one monitor, switch to using only one monitor while troubleshooting. 

    Open Premiere pro and load a default workspace, for example Window > Workspace > Edit. Then choose Window > Workspace > Reset workspace name, where workspace name is the name of the workspace you loaded. 

    Check your scratch disk settings, especially the Media Cache. If Premiere Pro is trying to use a disk that is no longer accessible, or a directory (folder) that is read-only, it causes strange problems. Do not use network drives. 

    Check that you have more than 20% of free disk space remaining on every hard drive.

items.name: Ren & Stimpy Wiki
items.title: Ren & Stimpy Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Ren & Stimpy Wiki!
items.desc:
Welcome to Ren & Stimpy Wiki, the collective database about the Nickelodeon television series The Ren & Stimpy Show that anyone can edit! 

The Ren & Stimpy Show, often simply Ren & Stimpy, is an American animated television series, created by Canadian animator John Kricfalusi for Nickelodeon. The series focuses on the titular characters: Ren Höek, a psychotic chihuahua, and Stimpson J. Cat, a good-natured, dimwitted cat. The show officially premiered on August 11, 1991, later the same day as the debut of Rugrats and Doug, the three of which comprised the original Nicktoons. The show ran for five seasons on the network, ending its original run with the Christmas episode "A Scooter for Yaksmas." The show was rated TV-Y7 on Nickelodeon/Nicktoons, and TV-PG on the Spike TV repeats.

items.name: Prison Break Wiki
items.title: Prison Break Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Prison Break Wiki
items.desc: Prison Break is an American television series that premiered on the Fox Network on August 29, 2005. The story revolves around a man who was sentenced to death for a crime he did not commit and his brother's elaborate plan to help him escape his death sentence. The serialized story structure of Prison Break is attributed to the format of storytelling adapted by the writers as each episode covers a part of the escape plan, a similar format used by Lost and 24. The first season of Prison Break was primarily filmed at Joliet Prison, which also contributed to the uniqueness of the show. Its success and recognition as a prison drama also revived interest in the genre.

Theatre usually implies a live event, usually involves humans, and is almost always intended to be performed before a live audience.

There are five seasons of this cult TV show. We welcome new users to come to the The Wire wiki to read, contribute, edit and more!

items.name: Tongue Tied
items.title: Tongue Tied
items.headline: Welcome to the Tongue Tied Wikia
items.desc: Welcome to Tongue Tied, a Red Dwarf encyclopedia that anyone can edit! Tongue Tied is a free Red Dwarf reference website that is being written collaboratively by the readers. This wikia's goal is to become the largest, most reliable, and most up-to-date encyclopedia about everything related to the Red Dwarf universe, presenting topics as they might appear if accessed in-universe.

items.name: Freeciv
items.title: Freeciv
items.headline: Welcome to the Freeciv Wiki!
items.desc:
The Freeciv Wiki is dedicated to Freeciv, which is a Free and Open Source empire-building strategy game inspired by the history of human civilization. The game commences in prehistory and your mission is to lead your tribe from the Stone Age to the Space Age...

Freeciv is much much more than a game: In Freeciv the game players can decide what the rules will be! This means that unlike nearly every other computer game, Freeciv can be a different game each time you play. This opportunity comes with some cost. Especially at first, a player trying to tackle all the subtleties and nuances of this complex gaming experience can get a little lost. 

We welcome new users to contribute to and edit the wiki!

items.name: Wikigrounds, the free Newgrounds encyclopedia
items.title: Wikigrounds, the free Newgrounds encyclopedia
items.headline: Wikigrounds, the Newgrounds Encyclopedia
items.desc: Newgrounds is the oldest, largest, and most prestigious Flash Portal in history. Since its origins in 1995, it has been the source of some of the most notable material on the internet, as a place where creators share their work with fans and each other. Learn about its games, movies, culture, and history on Wikigrounds.

items.name: San Francisco Homeless Resource
items.title: San Francisco Homeless Resource
items.headline: Welcome to the San Francisco Homeless Resource Wiki!
items.desc:
San Francisco Homeless Resource is a collaborative website for homeless advocates, providers, government and others in San Francisco. The wiki is a new evolution of how all parties helping the homeless can get together and share information efficiently and quickly.

The site can be updated by any user, so everyone can add and update information -- allowing much greater efficiency in serving the homeless community in San Francisco.

items.name: Futurepedia
items.title: Futurepedia
items.headline: Futurepedia, the Back to the Future Wiki
items.desc: Join Marty McFly and Doc Brown as they head back to the future in all of the adventures of the iconic trilogy by checking out Futurepedia, the Back to the Future Wiki. We strive to be a comprehensive resource of all three Back to the Future films and all the spinoff media, including the animated series, comics, novelizations, video games, and more. This wiki can be edited by anyone, including you, so come on in and share your knowledge and passion for Back to the Future!

items.name: OpenArena
items.title: OpenArena
items.headline: Review the OpenArena Wikia
items.desc: The OpenArena Wikia is a community-based fan site that was created as a means of promoting and chronicling information about the free game OpenArena. OpenArena is a free (as in freedom) network enabled multiplayer first person shooter based on the ioquake3 fork of the id tech 3 engine. On this community you will find character information, the manual, the FAQ, and map information.

items.name: Arrested Development Wiki
items.title: Arrested Development Wiki
items.headline: There are dozens of us. Dozens!
items.desc:
Arrested Development is a ground-breaking sitcom that originally aired 53 episodes over three seasons from November 2, 2003 to February 10, 2006 on FOX. 

Since cancellation it has developed a cult following and its popularity has grown - a fourth season is in post-production and a film is tentatively planned.

It follows family man Michael Bluth as he tries to keep his family and business from collapsing after his father George is sent to prison for embezzling money. As the family adjusts from riches to rags Michael helps his mother Lucille keep up appearances, sister Lindsay and brother-in-law Tobias with their failed marriage, son George Michael and niece Maeby through adolescence, and brothers Buster and G.O.B. adjust to working life.

items.name: Freeciv.org ジャパン
items.title: Freeciv.org ジャパン
items.headline: Civilizationライクな戦略シミュレーションゲーム「Freeciv」へようこそ！
items.desc:
『Freeciv』 はフリーのターン制多人数戦略ゲームです。 各プレイヤーはある一つの文明 (civilization) の指導者になり、 次の最終目標を目指して戦います。このコミュニティーでは『Freeciv』のマニュアル、ユニット、地形などゲームに関する情報を載せています。まだまだ情報が必要ですので皆様からの編集を歓迎します。

このコミュニティーで下記のことをすることができます。 
1、情報を編集することができます。
2、情報を提供することができます。
3、仲間を見つけてフォーラムで話したりすることが可能です。
4、仲間とチャットをすることもできます。

編集作業を行う場合はぜひぜひ、アカウントを登録してログインして下さい。

items.name: RareWiki

items.desc: Have you ever thought: "Hey, where can I learn everyting about Rare?". Have you every wondered: "What is a great wiki for one of the best video game companys?". Well, we have the answer: thee RareWiki! We have all you need to know about Rare, along with a blooming community. With everything from Banjo-Kazooie to Conkey and his friends, we are your best resource for your needs.

items.name: Supreme Commander Wiki
items.title: Supreme Commander Wiki
items.headline: Supreme Commander Wiki
items.desc: Supreme Commander Wiki is dedicated to Supreme Commander, a real-time strategy RTS game designed by Chris Taylor, set in a far future world. Although it was designed by Chris Taylor, it is not a sequel to his previous RTS, Total Annihilation, but rather a "spiritual successor", which implements the same gameplay mechanics and physics logic which was pioneered in Total Annihilation.

items.name: Fallout Wiki
items.title: Fallout Wiki
items.headline: Nukapedia - The Fallout Wiki
items.desc: Created and maintained by the Fallout community, Nukapedia: The Fallout Wiki aims to create the best resource for the Fallout series of games, including, but not limited to: Fallout, Fallout 2, Fallout 3, Fallout: New Vegas, Fallout 4, Fallout 76, Fallout: Tactics, Fallout: Brotherhood of Steel and Van Buren.

items.name: Darren Shan Wiki
items.title: Darren Shan Wiki
items.headline: Fly over to the Cirque du Freak Wiki!
items.desc: The Saga of Darren Shan (known in the U.S. as Cirque Du Freak) is a series of young adult vampire novels written by Darren O'Shaughnessy. They tell the story of a boy named Darren Shan who is turned into a half-vampire (blooded) by another vampire, Larten Crepsley. The Saga is made up of four trilogies and there is a film based on the first trilogy.

items.name: CAW Wrestling Wiki
items.title: CAW Wrestling Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the CAW Wrestling Wiki
items.desc:
The wiki about CAW Wrestling that anyone can edit.

Create-a-wrestler (CAW) is the name commonly given to a game mode in professional wrestling video games that allows modification of a base model and other related characteristics to create a unique character. The WWE series of games refers to these creations as superstars, and so the mode may also be identified as Create-a-Superstar (CAS).

items.name: SporeWiki

SporeWiki is a knowledge database dedicated to Spore, the computer simulation video game developed by Will Wright.  Affiliated with Sims Wiki, also developed by Wright, Spore is innovative in technology of the game design, as well as the expansive range of sci-fi game play.

SporeWiki has an active community who maintain unique projects such as the Taxonomy project and the SporeWiki Fiction Universe and any registered user is free to join.

items.desc: The Call of Duty Wiki is the number one place for Call of Duty information on the web. We host detailed information on everything Call of Duty; whether it be the campaign levels of Call of Duty 2 or the weapons from Call of Duty: Black Ops. We're currently working on over 8,800 pages, and we maintain around 29,000 images used to adorn our articles and gallery pages. We're always striving to improve our information, so feel free to stop down and join in! Or maybe you're just stuck on a level, or want to know more about your favorite weapon. We'll be able to help!

This wiki's job is to inform you about all things Carnivores, including the various areas, weapons, and animals available in all of the games, as well as covering companies, individuals, related games, and aspects of the fandom.

items.desc: NiGHTS into Dreams (or Nights into Dreams), is a video game released by Sega in 1996 for the Sega Saturn video game system. The game's story follows two children entering a dream world, where they are aided by a being called NiGHTS. This Wiki focuses on the the games and the characters of the NiGHTS universe, please contribute if you have something to add!

items.name: Assassin's Creed Wiki
items.title: Assassin's Creed Wiki
items.headline: Assassin's Creed Wiki
items.desc:
Assassin's Creed is a 2007 sandbox style action-adventure-stealth video game developed by Ubisoft Montreal and published by Ubisoft. The game was released for the Xbox 360 and PlayStation 3 in November 2007 and for PC in April 2008. It has since had several expansion versions and has expanded to PS4, XBox One and PC. 
With its thriving community, Assassin's Creed Wiki is an effort to document everything about the Assassin's Creed series, from basic game information to guides to the story. Be sure to also check out the Fan section.

items.name: Subculture Wiki
items.title: Subculture Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Subculture Wiki
items.desc: Welcome to the Subculture Wiki, a wiki is about subcultures! A subculture is a group of people with a set of ideals, philosophies, ethics, style, music or customs that exists within or outside, but not as a component of general culture or society. On this wiki, you can look up or write about a subculture or something related to a subculture.

items.name: The Bourne Directory
items.title: The Bourne Directory
items.headline: Welcome to the Bourne Directory Wiki!
items.desc: Please visit the Bourne Directory wiki! This wiki is a free, public, and collaborative encyclopedia dedicated to the original Robert Ludlum Bourne trilogy, its continuation by Eric van Lustbader, and the film series inspired by the novels. We always welcome new users to contribute to and edit the wiki!

items.name: Resistance Wiki
items.title: Resistance Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Resistance Wiki!
items.desc:
Resistance is a science-fiction horror series of first-person shooter and third-person shooter video games developed by Insomniac Games and published by Sony Computer Entertainment for the PlayStation 3, PlayStation Portable and PlayStation Vita game consoles. The series takes places in an alternate history around the year 1950's, in which an alien species known as the Chimera have invaded Earth and taken over all of Russia, and continue to invade and conquer much of Europe and the United States, expanding their armies by capturing humans and converting them into monstrous, super-powered soldiers to fight on their behalf. The player takes the role of one the sentinels, who are a few people injected with the Chimeran virus which grants them super abilities, like health renegeration.
The series is noted for its use of both conventional and futuristic weaponry, reflecting Insomniac's previous work on the Ratchet & Clank series.

items.name: The ReBoot Wiki
items.title: The ReBoot Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to The ReBoot Wikia
items.desc: The ReBoot Wikia is a community site dedicated to the Canadian CGI-animated action-adventure cartoon series ReBoot. If you are a fan of this series, or even if you're just curious about it, then this is the place for you! Come explore our content and help us expand this database... or join us in discussion about the characters, the episodes, or the series in general. All are welcome!

items.name: Eureka Wiki
items.title: Eureka Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Eureka Wiki!
items.desc: Eureka is an American science fiction television series that premiered on the Syfy channel. The show is set in a fictional town in the Pacific Northwest called Eureka, Oregon. Populated mostly by scientific geniuses working for Global Dynamics, an advanced research facility responsible for many technological breakthroughs. Each episode features a mysterious, accidental, or intentional misuse of technology, which the town sheriff, Jack Carter, then solves with the help of town scientists.

items.name: The Magic Tree House Wiki
items.title: The Magic Tree House Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Magic Tree House Wiki!
items.desc: The Magic Tree House Wiki is a database of information on Mary Pope Osbourne's fantasy series for young readers.  Come learn all about Jack, Annie, Kathleen and Teddy, Merlin, Morgan le Fay and more!  The database covers all the books, adventures and merchandise for the series and welcomes all who wish to contribute.

items.name: Unreal Wiki
items.title: Unreal Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Unreal Wikia!
items.desc: The Unreal Wiki is a wiki for Epic Games' Unreal video game series, including Unreal, Unreal Tournament, Unreal Championship, and various others. The player takes on the part of Prisoner 849, aboard the prison spacecraft Vortex Rikers. The ship was under way to a prison moon, but was pulled to an uncharted planet before reaching its destination. This wiki is focused on the events that take place during the games on the planet Na Pali. Users and fans of the Unreal series are encouraged to contribute!

items.name: AE Database
items.title: AE Database
items.headline: Astro Empires Databank
items.desc: Only the most extensive knowledge of the highly addicting browser based mmorts called astro empires. Come and see for youself and maybe you will come and join us. We have the latest news on Astro Empires, every update and everything you can possibly imagine, learn some tricks, and how to play. Best of all learn how to become the biggest threat in all of Astro Empires here!

items.name: Re-Volt Wiki
items.title: Re-Volt Wiki
items.headline: Drive over to the Re-Volt Wiki!
items.desc: Be welcome to Re-Volt Wiki: The wiki about the legendary radio control car racing video game from Acclaim, Re-Volt! Here is the right place to learn more about all the 49 RC cars and the 20 racing maps, besides the playmodes and weapons available. Our wiki is open for everyone to edit, so feel free to join us and help out with the database!

items.name: Reborn Wiki
items.title: Reborn Wiki
items.headline: Reborn Wiki, the wikia for everything Katekyō Hitman Reborn!
items.desc: Reborn Wiki is a community site created to give people an understanding and an interest in the anime and manga series, Katekyō Hitman Reborn! Here, you'll find everything from weapons and techniques, to chapters and episodes! Reborn Wiki has everything related to the Katekyō Hitman Reborn series! And if we've missed something, please help us add them.

items.name: One Tree Hill Wiki
items.title: One Tree Hill Wiki
items.headline: There is only One Tree Hill Wiki!
items.desc: One Tree Hill Wiki is an encyclopedia about One Tree Hill, a teen/young adult drama series created by Mark Schwahn. The series chronicled the lives of five high school friends, living in Tree Hill, whose lives collided when Lucas Scott joined his half-brother Nathan's high school basketball team. The initial animosity between the brothers, fueled by the influence of their often regretful parents, sparked a major confrontation which became thrice as fierce when three beautiful girls became further entwined in the brothers' lives. Lucas' best friend Haley James tested her loyalties and slowly started to fall for Nathan after breaking through his bad-boy persona; Peyton Sawyer struggled to choose between her head and her heart when it came to Lucas - even more so when her best friend, party-girl Brooke Davis, finally removed her facade and truly fell for the one-time outsider. All the lives of the five teenagers, and their friends, collided and drama was certain to follow.

items.title: Star Trek: The Continuing Mission Official Wiki

items.name: Fairly Odd Parents Wiki
items.title: Fairly Odd Parents Wiki
items.headline: The Fairly OddParents Wiki
items.desc: The Fairly OddParents Wiki is a guide to Nickelodeon's "The Fairly OddParents!" that includes comprehensive information on characters including Timmy Turner, Poof, Foop, Cosmo, Wanda, Mr. Crocker, Vicky the Babysitter, Jorgen Von Strangle, Chester, A.J., Tootie, Trixie Tang, Anti-Cosmo, Anti-Wanda, and more.

items.name: Team Fortress Wiki
items.title: Team Fortress Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Team Fortress Wiki
items.desc: Welcome to the Team Fortress Wiki! This site is an encyclopedic database about the two video games, "Team Fortress" and "Team Fortress 2". The Team Fortress Wiki is open to articles for any mods made for either of these games and in-detail stats for the game. Enter now to learn more and to help edit!

items.name: Alien Research
items.title: Alien Research
items.headline: Welcome to the Alien Research Wiki
items.desc: Welcome to the Alien Research Wiki, the extraterrestrial encyclopedia that anyone can edit! For all things extraterrestrial, this wiki is the place for avid fans or anyone curious about the topic. The Alien Research Wiki is a collection of information about events, facts, and types of extraterrestrials! Enter now to learn more and feel free to contribute in order to help the wiki grow.

items.name: Eureka Seven Wiki
items.title: Eureka Seven Wiki
items.headline: The biggest source of Eureka Seven information, the Eureka Seven Wiki!
items.desc: The Eureka Seven Wiki is the biggest library of information related to the entire Eureka Seven series on the web, including all anime episodes of Eureka Seven and Eureka Seven: AO, manga chapters, video games, entertainment, music, characters, and much more! Follow the story of Eureka and Renton Thurston in Eureka Seven, and their child, Ao, in Eureka Seven: AO. We hope to see you around!

items.name: Rest Stops and Service Plazas
items.title: Rest Stops and Service Plazas
items.headline: Take a rest at the Rest Stops Wikia
items.desc: Everyone has been traveling that long road at least once... then suddenly, hunger hits your stomach, or without warning, you realize how badly you need a bathroom. Your problem: you need a good place to stop, get things done, and get back on the road. We're here to help. We hope this wiki will grow to include information about rest stops the world over. Next time you're going on a road trip, stop by for the best advice. When you return, be sure to add information about any rest stops you visited along your way.

items.name: Greek TV Series Wiki
items.title: Greek TV Series Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Greek Wiki!
items.desc: Greek is an ABC comedy series following students of a fictional university who participate in their "Greek System". The series features the Kappa Tau Gamma, Omega Chi Delta, Lambda Sigma Omega fraternities and the Zeta Beta Zeta, Gamma Psi, Pi Pi Pi sororities along with many more. This Wikia features in-depth character descriptions and encourages Greek fans to edit!

items.name: WikiShrek
items.title: WikiShrek
items.headline: Welcome to WikiShrek
items.desc: The Shrek franchise is a series of movies featuring a green ogre named Shrek.   The original movie was critically acclaimed as an animated film worthy of adult interest, with many adult-oriented jokes and themes, but a simple enough plot and humor to appeal to children. It made notable use of pop music.  WikiShrek is a collaborative encyclopedia which covers all aspects of the series.

items.name: Street Fighter Wiki
items.title: Street Fighter Wiki
items.headline: Greetings and welcome to the comprehensive Street Fighter Wikia!
items.desc: Street Fighter Wiki is an encyclopedia for the iconic fighting game series; Street Fighter. The wiki itself is filled with information in regards to every facet of the Street Fighter series. Whether your interests are lore, tips, or you just wanna see what E. Honda's favorite hobby is, Street Fighter Wiki has it all.

items.name: The Secret World Wiki
items.title: The Secret World Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to The Secret World wiki!
items.desc: Welcome to The Secret World wiki! The Secret World is a Massively Multiplayer Online Role Playing Game (MMORPG, or just MMO) where players take control of a character from one of three factions, the Templars, Dragon, or Illuminati. It is described by its designers as "dark fantasy" and set in the modern day real world by developer Funcom. Ragnar Tørnquist is the creative director of the game.[
